              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Building Secure REST APIs with Node.js\",\n  \"content\": \"Security is paramount when building REST APIs. In this guide, we'll cover essential security practices including authentication, authorization, input validation, and protection against common vulnerabilities.\\n\\n## Key Security Measures\\n\\n### 1. Authentication\\n- Implement JWT-based authentication\\n- Use bcrypt for password hashing\\n- Enable refresh token mechanism\\n\\n### 2. Authorization\\n- Implement role-based access control\\n- Use middleware for permission checks\\n- Follow principle of least privilege\\n\\n### 3. Input Validation\\n- Validate all user inputs\\n- Sanitize data to prevent injections\\n- Use express-validator\\n\\n### 4. Security Headers\\n- Use Helmet.js\\n- Enable CORS properly\\n- Set CSP headers\\n\\n### 5. Rate Limiting\\n- Prevent brute force attacks\\n- Implement API throttling\\n- Use express-rate-limit\",\n  \"excerpt\": \"A comprehensive guide to building secure REST APIs with Node.js, covering authentication, authorization, and security best practices.\",\n  \"category\": \"programming\",\n  \"tags\": [\"nodejs\", \"security\", \"rest-api\", \"express\"],\n  \"featuredImage\": \"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558494949-ef010cbdcc31?w=800\",\n  \"status\": \"draft\"\n}"
